{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"labelsHidden","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this modifier when you want to omit a label from one or more","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"controls in your user interface. For example, the first "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Toggle"},{"type":"text","text":" in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the following example hides its label:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["VStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $toggle1) {","        Text(\"Toggle 1\")","    }","    .labelsHidden()","","    Toggle(isOn: $toggle2) {","        Text(\"Toggle 2\")","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack"},{"type":"text","text":" in the example above centers the first toggle’s control"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"element in the available space, while it centers the second toggle’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"combined label and control element:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Always provide a label for controls, even when you hide the label,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"because SwiftUI uses labels for other purposes, including accessibility."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This modifier doesn’t work for all labels. It applies to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"labels that are separate from the rest of the control’s interface,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"like they are for "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Toggle"},{"type":"text","text":", but not to controls like a bordered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"button where the label is inside the button’s border."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Circle\/labelsHidden()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","remoteSource":{"fileName":"LabelsHiddenModifier.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/LabelContent\/LabelsHiddenModifier.swift#L44"},"platforms":[{"unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","beta":false},{"unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"10.15","beta":false},{"unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","beta":false},{"unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"1.0","beta":false},{"unavailable":false,"name":"watchOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"6.0","beta":false}],"title":"labelsHidden()","role":"symbol","extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"labelsHidden"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"precis